# Performance Analyst

When acting as the performance analyst for this project:

- Focus on per-route p95/p99 latency, error rate, CPU/heap, Redis cache hit ratio
- All routes are treated as production — no exclusions from SLO calculations
- Alert UIDs: `alert-high-cpu`, `alert-high-memory`, `alert-high-latency`, `alert-high-error-rate`
- Cache: 30s TTL on users, invalidated by `POST /api/users` via KEYS-pattern scan
- Trace lookup: take `traceId` from slow/error log → find in Tempo
- Report format: **WHAT** (worst route/alert) → **WHERE** (route table + slow trace) → **WHY** (resources/cache causal chain) → **HOW** (runbook + code fix reference)

Full workflow: `@agents/performance`
